@startuml Customer_Journey_Sequence

actor Customer
participant "Mahapurush Mandir System" as System
database "Database" as DB

== Authentication (Login) ==

Customer -> System: Provide Credentials (Email, Password)
activate System
System -> DB: Verify User Credentials
activate DB
DB --> System: User Identification & Roles
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Redirect to Customer Dashboard

== Information & Media ==

Customer -> System: Browse Gallery Categories
System -> DB: Fetch Categories & Images
activate DB
DB --> System: Image Data
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Display Gallery

== Rituals & Services (Pooja Booking) ==

Customer -> System: Select Pooja Type & Date
System -> DB: Fetch Fee and Check Availability
activate DB
DB --> System: Availability & Fee Data
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Show Booking Form
Customer -> System: Submit Booking Request
System -> DB: Insert Booking Record (Status: Pending)
activate DB
DB --> System: Success
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Confirm Booking Request

== Devotion & Support (Donations) ==

Customer -> System: Initiate Donation
System -> DB: Record Donation Request
activate DB
DB --> System: Success
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Navigate to Payment Gateway
Customer -> System: Complete Payment Successfully
System -> DB: Update Payment & Donation Status
activate DB
DB --> System: Success
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Provide Donation Receipt

== Community Engagement (Events) ==

Customer -> System: View Upcoming Events
System -> DB: Fetch Event List
activate DB
DB --> System: List of Active Events
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Show Events
Customer -> System: Register for an Event
System -> DB: Insert Participant Record
activate DB
DB --> System: Success
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Confirm Participation

== Records & History ==

Customer -> System: Request History (Pooja/Donations)
System -> DB: Query History Tables
activate DB
DB --> System: Personal Usage Records
deactivate DB
System -> Customer: Display History & Downloadable Receipts

== Termination (Logout) ==

Customer -> System: Logout
System -> System: Destroy Session
System -> Customer: Redirect to Homepage
deactivate System

@enduml
